original: Dittmer, Torsten Ernfrid William, kyrkoherde. Vikingstad, f. 29/10/92 i Gbg av tygförvalt. Fr. D. o. Elna Akesdotter. G. 21 m. Stanny Lindmark. Barn: Torgny f. 24, Elna-britta 27. — Stud :ex. i Kristianstad 13, fil. kand. 17, fil. mag. 18, provår 22, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Linköp. stift 30. Ämneslär. v. folkhögsk., h. folksk. samt komm. mellansk. 18-30, v. kommin. 30, tf. kyrkoh. i Vikingstad 30, kyrkoh. där sed. 31. Ordf. i kyrko- o. past:-stämmor samt i folksk :styr. i Vikingstad o. Sjögestad m. m.
translated: Dittmer, Torsten Ernfrid William, pastor. Born on October 29, 1892 in Gothenburg to parents Fr. D. and Elna Akesdotter, who worked in the textile industry. Married to Stanny Lindmark in 1921, and has two children: Torgny born in 1924 and Elna-britta born in 1927. Education: Completed studies in Kristianstad in 1913, received a Bachelor's degree in Philosophy in 1917, a Master's degree in Philosophy in 1918, a probationary year in 1922, a Bachelor's degree in Theology, a practical theological examination and was ordained as a pastor in the Linköping diocese in 1930. Worked as a core curriculum teacher in adult education schools, high schools, and middle schools from 1918 to 1930, became an assistant pastor in 1930, acted as an interim pastor in Vikingstad in 1930, and became the official pastor there in 1931. Also served as chairman of the church and parish meetings, as well as on the board of directors for elementary schools in Vikingstad and Sjögestad.
